cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL

The paper discusses a computer vision challenge focused on satellite image understanding, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the potential impact of this research on global urban planning and climate change, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The evaluation criteria and baselines provided in the paper also suggest a focus on machine learning, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze satellite imagery, which could potentially place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
